Date: Tue, 8 Nov 2016 17:37:37 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing options to man.1 and man2html.1 man pages

---
 man/en/man.man      | 7 +++++--
 man2html/man2html.1 | 6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/man/en/man.man b/man/en/man.man
index d576d9e..9482385 100644
--- a/man/en/man.man
+++ b/man/en/man.man
@@ -21,7 +21,7 @@
 man \- format and display the on-line manual pages
 .SH SYNOPSIS
 .B man 
-.RB [ \-acdfFhkKtwW ]
+.RB [ \-acdfFhkKtvVwW ]
 .RB [ --path ] 
 .RB [ \-m 
 .IR system ] 
@@ -176,9 +176,12 @@ Equivalent to
 .BR \-\^F " or " \-\-preformat
 Format only - do not display.
 .TP
-.B \-\^h
+.BR \-\^h " or " \-\-help
 Print a help message and exit.
 .TP
+.BR \-\^v ", " \-\^V " or " \-\-version
+Print version information and exit.
+.TP
 .B \-\^k
 Equivalent to
 .BR apropos .
diff --git a/man2html/man2html.1 b/man2html/man2html.1
index c1c25b3..5862e28 100644
--- a/man2html/man2html.1
+++ b/man2html/man2html.1
@@ -70,6 +70,12 @@ from a cgi script.
 .TP
 .B \-\^E string
 Output an error page containing the given error message.
+.TP
+.BR \-\^v " or " \-\^V
+Output page containing version information.
+.TP
+.B \-\^f
+Unused, kept for backward compatibility.
 .LP
 The general form of a hyperlink generated for a man page reference is
 .IP
